tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control. Cholesterol, triglycerides, and chloride are also mildly elevated, suggesting increased cardiovascular risk and possible metabolic syndrome. Renal function and electrolytes are within normal limits, and there is no evidence of microalbuminuria. Recommend review of diabetes and lipid management.
